  "poem": {
    "content": "The wind, a coyote's lonely cry,\nupon the mountain, etched so high.\nI push against the icy air,\na viable escape, beyond compare.\n\nMy skis carve lines, a mesh of white,\nwhile shadows lengthen in the fading light.\nA distant antenna, stark and cold,\na story whispered, yet untold.\n\nThe actual danger, starts to bite,\nthe tiger in my soul takes flight.\nA reckless hip, a sudden fall,\nI pray for rescue, hear the call.\n\nA good samaritan, through snow appears,\nerasing doubt, dispelling fears.\nHis weathered face, a living tool,\nto mend the spirit, break the cruel\n\ntattoo of the past, to start anew,\nand inspire hope, fresh and true.\nHe lifts me gently, from the snow,\nviable again, lets courage grow.",
